	   <a name=98346965397414></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98346965397414><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98346965397414>Soloing a Shaman lvl 14 to 23</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98346965397414#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 1st 1:00 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At lvl 14 a shaman begins to change from melee based to mana based attacks.&nbsp;&nbsp;They gain their last melee skill and obtain some great spells.  A shaman can now root and nuke like a wiz.  They can kite like a druid.  And they get an upgread to the slow line of spells to help off set their faltering melee skill.  In general life is good for the soloing shaman.  However by lvl 19 it becomes harder and harder to solo.  Our melee skill are no match for most mobs and we don't have the buffs to compensate.  Compaired to druids and wizerds we have small mana reserves and can't kite or root and nuke effectivly.  ( I am speaking of untwinked shaman). <br><br>During this time it is important to keep your melee skill up.  I feel the best way to solo a shaman at these lvls is as follows<br><br>Pull the mob with Spirit Strike.  Kite the mob until you have only enough mana to cast Affliction and walking sleep.  Cast afflection, run, cast walking sleep and melee the mob to death.  Even if you have the mana to kill while kiting it is a good idea to melee at the end.  This will keep your melee skills up.  <br><br>Spiders, and bugs are great mobs for shaman during these lvls.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
