<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=9835027648528></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9835027648528><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9835027648528>RE: Soloing a Shaman lvl 14 to 23</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9835027648528#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>158 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 1st 10:12 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>While I agree with your post on some things, I also disagree.&nbsp;&nbsp;I will point them out as I go =)  Please take this as intended.  My view of the Shaman class.  I make no claims as to this is "how it is".<br><br>To some extent Shaman change from "melee based" to "mana based" at level 14, but you will find you can still do the vast majority of your damage with a solid weapon.  Spirit strike has a nice punch at level 14.  I mean 75 mana for 74 damage is quite nice at that level.  But that 75 mana is a &gt;lot&lt; at level 14.  I think that casting two tainted breaths for 80 mana and doing around 120 damage is a much better deal.  Yes, tainted breath takes longer to work, but it is MUCH more efficient.  We can not "root and nuke like a wiz."  The reason I say this is look at their level 12 spell shock of lightning.  60 mana for 80 damage at level 14.  That is almost a 35% increase in damage per mana point spent!  Leave the nuking to magicians, wizards, and druids.  Save your nukes for emergencies.<br><br>A Shaman also can not kite like a druid.  Oh, sure, we can a little, but we lack one thing that druids have that makes them the king of non fear kiting (necros own that one):  snare.  Yes, with SoW we can outrun most mobs.  But we have to run forever and a day to get the separation we need to get a nuke off.  Snare allows more separation more quickly.  Just on that, a druid can kite, med, kite three mobs to our two.  And with the nerfs to DoT damage on moving mobs made a long time ago, DoT kiting isn't any more efficient that nuke kiting.  Druids also (eventually) get a better mana to damage ratio than Shaman nukes.<br><br>Life can be good for the soloing shaman.  I disagree with your assertion that soloing becomes harder and harder at 19.  Yes, until you hit level 24 soloing can be rough if you are not real familiar with the mobs that are easy to take at that level.  But at 24, solo life for the Shaman get a huge shot in the arm.  Envenomed Breath is such a huge improvement, you will wonder if you are playing the same character.  Also Frost Strike strengthens your take down ability.<br><br>The myth that Shaman have much lower mana pools than a similar level druid or int based class is just that, a myth.  10 points of wisdom separate the maximum base Wis from a Barbarian Shaman and a Wood Elf or Halfling Druid.  At level 20 that is about 40 mana.  That is a single extra SoW, about half of a DoT or Nuke.  Granted an Erudite Wizard with a max base Int has a bigger gap.  That comes out to 128 extra mana, but is also a 37 point difference.  But let's see that wizard match the ac, hp, and melee damage output of a Shaman.  The wizard gets a mob's attention and dies.  We absorb (slowed) hits and keep on ticking.<br><br>Yes, keep those melee and defense skills up.  Especially defense.  Defense is HUGELY important.  More AC = fewer hits and less damage on a hit.  You will learn to love it, especially once you break 800 AC later on in life.<br><br>Here is how I prefer to see a solo shaman fight.  It can be done a couple of ways.  Pull with slow.  Time a DoT between hits, melee, maybe nuke once, watch mob die, heal afterwards.  Or Root, DoT, med, reroot and redot when they wear off.  Both of these make MUCH better use than going OOM every fight.  If you walk away with 40m after healing (if you need to that is) that is 40m less you have to meditate back and can be killing again that much quicker.  I still solo quite happily with no Uber gear at level 51 with either of those methods.  Granted, with a pet and regeneration spells (which you get at 24) there is some variation, but the basics remain the same.<br><br>Don't try to be another class.  A shaman that does will NOT be successful.  Learn your skills and spells.  This will in turn make your mana go much further, and make you MUCH more deadly.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>Drindal<br>43 Monk BB<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
