	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have to go with Gorthin on this one. At 20 I will pull with Affliction and follow up with Tainted Breath. By then the mob has come upon me and then I Root it and med. When Tainted wears off I recast it. When Root wears off I recast it. Normally the mobs dies right about the time Affliction wears off. I always try and melee near the end to save on mana. DD is NOT the way to go. DoTs should be used as intended and are much more mana efficient. NOT DD! My wisdom, as of right now, is only 117 and I can usually kill an even con and have enough mana left over to heal myslef, or whatever. Clearly every Shammy should discover what works best for him or her, and at what level, and against which mobs. I've read many of Gorthin's posts on Shamans and I find him to be informed, rational, and, at times, cleverly entertaining. There is NO one way to solo as a Shaman. I think we can all agree on that. As a footnote, I wonder why so many posts of questionable legitimacy are written anonymously? Any thoughts on that? Hmm?<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
