	   <tr><td colspan=2>This will be my last reply to this thread as I can see it getting chippy.&nbsp;&nbsp;Remember these are MY OPINIONS.<br><br>Actually, level 9 and tainted breath begins the mana = damage phase of a Shaman's life.  40 mana for 60 damage is an excellent deal at this level.  Yes, at 14, you can burn stuff down quickly compared to before.  But it is still not the way to go, at least not exclusively.<br><br>And I still say if you root/nuke or "kite" from 14 to 19, you are cheating yourself of playing time.  Why pick up a bad habit now?  Root/DoT &gt;can&lt; work from 9 on.  I would personally wait until 24 before I made it a habit.  Stick with melee, slow, DoT, and nuke.<br><br>And I still disagree as to the "power".  From 14 to 60, not just 23,  the "power" of a Shaman is a) Slow, b) DoTs c) Melee (gets less important later on) and d) a &gt;little&lt; nuking.  If you want to minimize your dowtime at &gt;any&lt; level, nuking should be done as little as possible.  Of course, this is out the window if you need to burn (freeze) something down quickly.  Then mana efficiency is not a priority.<br><br>Twinks are twinks.  That 189 wisdom at level 20 is about 55 more than an untwinked, non funded character will see.  It is like comparing apples and oranges.  That extra wisdom and mana serve NO purpose solo except to make you med to full longer.  If the mob you are fighting takes more than 1 slow, one DoT, melee and one nuke, it is too big for you.  We are not Druids who try to go mana happy to quad kite later on in life.  Most druids also now acknowledge that wisdom beyond 170ish is a waste of time and is hogging AC.  Ever see a level 50+ Druid get shredded in 10 seconds in a dungeon, because of a bad defense skill and crappy AC items?  It is not pretty.  "Druid down.  Find someone with a Rez stick."<br><br>Anyway, if you manage a 189 wisdom at that level (20 or earlier), you should not be having problems soloing through to 24.  If you are...  *shrug*  Go play a Necro or Magician for the solo power.<br><br>I am just telling you what my experiences were pre-kunark, pre-twinking.  I was the baddest Shaman on the block with a RTS and almost full banded at 19.  Sounds pathetic, eh?  But I still managed to solo.  It was because I used my mana as efficiently as possible.  I can not count the number of times I was glad I saved the mana I would have used nuking for emergency roots to run, or for healing, resowing, etc etc.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>Drindal<br>43 Monk BB<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
