	   <tr><td colspan=2>Envenomed Bolt is great.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is some good (tm).  But, IMO, it is not the main thing a Shaman at that level should be doing.  You will generally be so busy a) buffing everyone b) Slowing mobs c) Backup healing and d) Root parking that 320 mana becomes prohibitive.<br><br>If you have the mana, great, use it.  But slowing is our #1 priority in a "normal" group.  Also, pulling that cleric's arse out of the fire when he aggro heals is often our job as well *wink*<br><br>To answer your question, as I believe Badjur pointed out, all of our poison DoTs stack.  Go ahead and use Venom of the Snake if you have the urge to DoT, but don't want to spend the full 320 mana.  160 Mana for VoS vs 320 for Eb leaves you with another Gheal, or a big chunk of a Sheal if you are 51+<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>Drindal<br>43 Monk BB<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
