	   <tr><td colspan=2>My intent is to compair diffrent weapons a shaman may choose to use at diffrent stages of his/her life.&nbsp;&nbsp;There are at least 4 stages in the life of a shaman lvl 1-13, lvl 14-23, lvl 24-33, and lvl 34+.  <br><br>the damage rate refered to is calculated by deviding 100 (times the weapon's damage) devide by the delay.  <br><br>Before lvl 14 the shaman is lettle more than a week warrior who used magic to agument his melee.  Therefore the weapons damage rate should be the deciding factor in choosing which weapon to use.  The following weapons are found in newbee zones.  <br>Rusty spear  damage 5 delay 38  damage rate 13.1<br>Splintering Club     4      28              14.3<br>cracked staff       5       32              15.6<br><br>And the winner is.... the cracked staff.  Infact for a shaman the cracked staff is as good as any weapon before fine steel.  <br><br>At or about lvl 10 a shaman should be ready to upgrade his/her weapon.  The following weapons are the most common choices:<br>Weapon           Damade        Delay     Rate<br>FS Spear           6             27       22.2<br>FS Morning star    8             38       21.1<br>Screaming Mace     8             35       22.8<br>FS Great Staff     9             36       25<br>Runed Totem Staff  9             37       24.3<br>Bloodforged Hammer 13            50       26.  <br><br>Here the two hand blunts have the advantage in damage.  It should be noted that the BFH has a damage cap on it until lvl 20 so it dose the same average damage as the RTS.  In the early days too many young shaman were getting their hands on this mighty weapon....grin how times have changed.<br><br>When you switch from your one hand weapon to a two hand blunt you should use 20 training points to get your skill up.  <br><br>Yes I know your at lvl 14 and still have no weapons skill with a spear.  And yes I know the epic weapon is a spear.  Howeve you have more than enough time to develop this skill and I see no reason to you an inferior weapon at this stage of your life.  After all the only real damage you can do at this stage is with your weapon, so you might as well do as much as you can.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
