	   <a name=98323667341872></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98323667341872><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98323667341872>RE: lvl 1 troll shammy</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98323667341872#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2076><span id=Sage>Pusbag</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>1379 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Feb 26th 8:17 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.72]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hunt in "Da Swamp" until you are L5-6 and then head to Freeport to get a bind at the secret entrance to the underground tunnels.&nbsp;&nbsp;Once you have gotten your bind go to West Commonlands and hunt those orcs located on the north face of the zone.<br><br>Look for my guide on hunting as a young shammy.  It is what I used until I was in my teens.<br>Good luck!<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br><br>**************************************************<br>I beg the forgiveness of those who have now seen this 3 or 4 times.  It's just easier for me to pull it up and repost for the noobs.<br><br>From level 6 there is a wonderful place to park your troll itchy butt (or your nekulturny @$$, if you are a Barbie doll) in the wonderful land of West Commonlands. <br><br>Let me preface this guide with the observation that many of us live a hard scrabble life in the early stages attempting to gain access to a workable group in which there is little chance of dying, yet in which the rewards are great. Hence, the East Commonlands orcs are frequently overcamped lending credibility to the view that working the orcs is much like visiting Disneyland-- huge crowds, long waits, and brief periods of frenetic activity. A chore, to say the least. <br><br>That said, there is a wonderland waiting to unfold its' beauty for you right next door: West Commonlands. True, it's no secret that WC is a fine hunting ground for many levels, but what sets it apart from the others is the exquisite balance between safety, challenge, and reward for the younger members of our class. <br><br>Go, young shammy, to the orc camp located on the north face of the wall midway between the eastern and westernmost edges of the zone. If you are truly a newbie and you haven't bought the "True North" spell and your Sense Heading does not fire off a cardinal direction for you, there are two ways to determine your orientation: <br>1) Drop a sword or knife on the ground (the one you picked up off the orc pawn you saw wandering by) and examine the direction the business end-- the sharp and dangerous part-- is pointing towards; that will be North. <br>2) Look up in the sky and observe the clouds. Contary to the weather phenomenon located here in the United States, clouds in Norrath move east to west. Unfortunately, this only helps you in daylight. <br><br>Once you have arrived at the orc camp turn so you are facing the enemy. You will notice that there are six orc centurians of various levels standing around and quite possibly a legionaire among them. If you observe carefully, you will see that there is an orc standing by himself on the easternmost edge of the camp, two orcs in the middle, and three orcs on the western portion of the camp. This is significant in that the three groups are not social with each other. In other words, if you pull the eastern orc from the front of the camp he will not drag the other five orcs along with him. Notice the difference from the orc camps in East Commonlands? You pull from those camps while you are solo and all H, E, double hockey sticks breaks loose. However, in WC you can modulate how much you wish to train depending on your levels and/or skills. <br>Once you have leveled up or your confidence exceeds your abilities you can work on the two orcs in the center. Or the three on the left side of the camp. Your choice! You will notice though that I said pull from the front of the camp. If you choose to pull catty-whumpus from some other angle you are likely to grab your intended prey and also the orcs whose paths they cross as well. This too, is significant, because unlike many who park themselves on the ground in front of whatever it is they are hunting, I have a much better place for you to rest/med/heal. <br>Standing in front of the camp again, look to your right. See the ridgeline that comes out from the north face of the wall? Walk up that ridge staying on the pinnicle the whole way. You will come to a flat wide open space well above the plains of West Commonlands. This location is key. You can place yourself here and relax, go get a sandwich, drink a beer, whatever, and not have to worry about getting killed from passing Hill Giants, Kodiaks, or wandering legos. This is one of those places in the game where no mob ever goes on its' own volition. Even better, as a level 6 shammy (troll, I hope!) you can pull from this location! Once you have gathered the courage-- in casted or bottled form-- move along the ridge line just past the tree obstructing your view of the lone orc standing by the fire. Cast that all powerful spell you have conveniently memmorized on the orc and run back to the flat spot to await the grateful centurian's thanks for your display of magical prowess. Engage him at will! Loot that corpse! Sell that Deathfist belt! <br>The only problem with this location is others who choose to hunt orcs will not see you up there and will assume the camp is empty. Coordinate accordingly, split the spawn, continue to improve your skills. <br>You can remain here well into L13 and enjoy the added benefit of SoWing high level characters for pay as they make their run from the Freeport area to Kithicor Forest and beyond. They have to go by the camp on their way to the Karanas and often advertise that they are paying to get SoWed. <br>There you have it, young shammy. Riches, fame, the spilling of orc blood. What more could a troll want? <br>Good luck and say "Hello" if you see me on the Druzzil Ro server! <br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
