	   <tr><td colspan=2>What you keep hearing about is the shaman epic quest weapon, Spear of Fate.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you ever plan on doing the quest (and if you work on your shaman to mid 50's or so, you probably will want to), upping your piercing skill would be a good idea.  Don't put any more practices into piercing.  Get you a piercing weapon and get your skill up the good old fashioned way (by using it).  While in group, melee with your piercing weapon as much as possible (blue cons or better), and your skill will go up in time.<br><br>You're right.  Piercing weapons do not do the damage that a 2hb does.  I lost the roll last night on a Frost Giant Femur (grrrr)...BUT had the good fortune to be able to actually use it, and I was VERY impressed (50 pts dmg first hit), and then DEPRESSED that I lost  lol.<br><br>I currently use a Spine Chill Spear and like it even better than the Jade Chokidai Prod I lusted after for so many levels and finally managed to camp at lvl 34.<br><br>By the way...Spear of Fate is an awesome and impressive looking weapon   :)   Funny, I never go for items simply for what they look like, but this spear is absolutely beautiful &lt;drools&gt;<br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur<br>Oracle of Novus Invictus<br>(Druzzil Ro)<br><br>Aepox Weeblatter<br>51 Dwarf Warrior</td></tr>
